Mix margarine, peanut butter, sugar and egg. Stir in baking powder, baking soda, salt and flour. Chill dough for several hours or overnight. Roll dough into 1 1/4 inch balls. Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten crisscross style with a fork dipped in flour or sugar. Bake for 10 minutes at 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).